++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

In normal Dockerfiles:
Everything stays inside final image:

npm cache
temporary files
build tools
unwanted layers
Result:

larger image

🚀 Solution → Multi-stage Build

Docker allows:
multiple FROM statements
Each FROM creates a separate stage.

📦 Stage 1 — Builder Stage
FROM node:18-alpine AS builder
This creates a temporary build environment.
Think like:
"Workspace for preparing application"
Inside it:
install dependencies
build app
prepare files

🔍 What Happens Here

WORKDIR /app
COPY package.json .
RUN npm install
COPY . .

Container filesystem becomes:

/app
 ├── node_modules
 ├── package.json
 ├── server.js

This stage is named:
builder

🚀 Stage 2 — Production Stage

Now:

FROM node:18-alpine

IMPORTANT:
This starts a:
completely fresh new image
Previous stage does NOT automatically continue.

Think like:
new clean container

🔥 Why Fresh Image?
Because we only want:
necessary application files
clean production image

NOT:
temporary build files
cache
unnecessary layers

✅ Then:
WORKDIR /app

Creates working directory in NEW image.
Equivalent to:
mkdir /app
cd /app

inside container.

🚀 MOST IMPORTANT LINE
COPY --from=builder /app /app

🔍 Meaning

This means:
Copy files FROM builder stage
📦 Source
/app

inside:
builder stage

📦 Destination
/app
inside:
new production image
🧠 Visual Understanding

Stage 1 (builder)
builder stage
----------------
/app
 ├── node_modules
 ├── package.json
 ├── server.js
Stage 2 (production)

Starts EMPTY:
production stage
----------------
(empty)

Then:
COPY --from=builder /app /app
copies prepared application into final image.

🚀 Why This Is Powerful

Because:
builder stage can contain extra tools
final image remains clean/minimal

This is EXTREMELY common in:

React apps
Angular apps
Java apps
Go apps
Production CI/CD

🔥 Real Production Example

In React:
Builder stage:
npm install
npm run build

Final stage:
only static HTML files copied to nginx
Huge optimization.

🧠 Important Concept

Each FROM:

resets filesystem
creates new stage
creates separate image layer chain

So we explicitly transfer needed files using:
COPY --from

🚀 Simple Analogy

Think like:
Stage	Purpose

Builder Kitchen	Prepare food
Production Plate	Serve only final food

You don’t serve:

raw ingredients
utensils
garbage

Only final clean output 👍

